cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.CR

This paper deals with information retrieval and analysis methods for disease tracking using publicly available documents on the internet. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also uses natural language processing techniques such as recurrent neural networks and Naive Bayes log count ratio, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses classification performance, which could place it in cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper deals with public health events, which could suggest it belongs to cs.CY (Computers and Society) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
